thods for handling transaction states. I'm also wondering about the visibility of methods and how reflection works with public and non-public classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering public classes**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how public classes nested inside each other shouldn't be an issue. However, public methods might have some concerns regarding line length. I need to figure out what specific guidelines or best practices I should follow when writing these methods. It could help to check resources or tools that assist with formatting and organization to ensure everything is clean and readable. Let’s make sure to address these points clearly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_g9NN0jeea6ApdS3sX1Mk3yQ7|fc_0f2141aef0866d1a016a424ae53dcc8195a9653bf96fa32172", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "dependencies {\n    testImplementation \"net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n", "newText": "dependencies {\n    testImplementation \"net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'javax.transaction:jta:1.1'\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 8603, "output": 1719, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31826, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782729419454, "responseId": "resp_0f2141aef0866d1a016a424acc020c8195a3d50a237030d07e"}}
